  <dashboards>
    <dashboard name='Healthcare Aanlytics Story' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Segoe UI Black' italic='true'>Healthcare Analytics Story: </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Segoe UI Black' italic='true'>A Visual Insight into Patient Demographics, Department Performance and Treatment Outcomes</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1028' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1216' minheight='964' minwidth='1216' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98684' x='658' y='830'>
            <zone h='10062' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98684' x='658' y='830' />
            <zone fixed-size='155' h='16079' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98684' x='658' y='10892' />
            <zone h='72199' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98684' x='658' y='26971'>
              <flipboard active-id='11' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='This healthcare analytics story provides a comprehensive visual overview of hospital performance based on patient demographics, admission trends, department-wise revenue, disease distribution, and treatment outcomes. By transforming raw hospital data into meaningful visual insights, the dashboard enables healthcare management to monitor patient inflow, evaluate departmental efficiency, understand disease prevalence, and assess recovery rates. These insights support data-driven decision-making for effective resource allocation, improved patient care, and strategic planning within the hospital.This dashboard presents insights on patient admissions, department revenue, disease distribution, and patient outcomes for better decision making.This dashboard provides an overview of hospital operations including patient admissions, department revenue, disease distribution, and patient outcomes. It helps hospital management monitor performance and resource utilization.&#10;&#10;' captured-sheet='Healthcare Analytics' id='1' />
                  <story-point caption='Overall Hospital Performance Indicators:&#10;This section highlights the total patients admitted, total revenue generated, and the average medical cost per patient which provides an overview of hospital performance.&#10;&#10;' captured-sheet='KPI' id='4'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='KPI'>
                        <filter class='categorical' column='[federated.0wfbc6o1i18im51bnst9g1fkhtbh].[none:Department:nk]'>
                          <groupfilter function='level-members' level='[none:Department:nk]' user:ui-enumeration='all' user:ui-marker='enumerate' />
                          <target field='[federated.0wfbc6o1i18im51bnst9g1fkhtbh].[none:Department:nk]' />
                        </filter>
                        <filter class='categorical' column='[federated.0wfbc6o1i18im51bnst9g1fkhtbh].[none:Insurance:nk]'>
                          <groupfilter function='level-members' level='[none:Insurance:nk]' user:ui-enumeration='all' user:ui-marker='enumerate' />
                          <target field='[federated.0wfbc6o1i18im51bnst9g1fkhtbh].[none:Insurance:nk]' />
                        </filter>
                        <selection-collection />
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Monthly Admission Trend:&#10;The admission trend indicates variations in patient inflow throughout the year and helps in understanding peak demand periods.The monthly admission trend shows fluctuations in patient inflow across the year. The hospital experienced peak admissions during mid-year months, indicating higher demand for healthcare services and increased pressure on hospital resources.&#10;&#10;' captured-sheet='Monthy Patients Admission' id='5' />
                  <story-point caption='Department Revenue Analysis:&#10;The Cardiology department generates the highest revenue among all departments followed by ICU and General Medicine. This indicates a higher number of specialized treatments and resource utilization in these departments.&#10;' captured-sheet='Department Revenue' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='Age Group Wise Disease:&#10;Patients aged above 60 are more prone to chronic diseases such as hypertension and heart disease. This suggests the need for improved geriatric care facilities and specialized treatment programs for elderly patients.&#10;' captured-sheet='Age Group Wise Disease' id='7' />
                  <story-point caption='Gender Distribution:&#10;The gender distribution shows a nearly equal proportion of male and female patients admitted to the hospital, indicating balanced healthcare accessibility.&#10;' captured-sheet='Gender Distribution' id='8' />
                  <story-point caption='Disease Distribution:&#10;Heart disease and diabetes are the most common diagnoses among patients, highlighting the increasing prevalence of lifestyle-related diseases.&#10;' captured-sheet='Disease Treemap' id='9' />
                  <story-point caption='Outcome Analysis:&#10;A majority of patients have successfully recovered after treatment, demonstrating effective medical care and hospital service quality.&#10;' captured-sheet='Outcome Analysis' id='10' />
                  <story-point caption='Management Insights and Strategic Recommendations:&#10;• The analysis indicates that departments such as Cardiology and ICU experience higher patient inflow and contribute significantly to hospital revenue. Therefore, hospital management should allocate additional medical staff, equipment, and bed capacity to these departments to improve service efficiency and reduce patient waiting time.&#10;&#10;• The average length of patient stay suggests a high level of hospital bed utilization. Implementing effective discharge planning and patient flow management strategies can enhance bed availability and allow the hospital to accommodate more patients during peak periods.&#10;&#10;• Disease distribution analysis highlights a growing prevalence of lifestyle-related illnesses such as heart disease and diabetes. This suggests the need for preventive healthcare initiatives including regular health check-ups, awareness programs, and early diagnosis facilities.&#10;&#10;• Patients belonging to the age group above 60 years are more prone to chronic diseases and require long-term medical attention. This indicates the necessity for developing specialized geriatric care units and improving elderly healthcare services within the hospital.&#10;&#10;• A significant proportion of patients rely on insurance coverage for medical treatment. Strengthening partnerships with insurance providers can improve patient accessibility to healthcare services and ensure stable revenue generation for the hospital.&#10;&#10;• Monthly admission trends reveal fluctuations in patient inflow across different periods. Hospital management should adopt strategic resource planning during peak months to prevent overcrowding and ensure quality patient care.&#10;&#10;• The outcome analysis shows that a majority of patients have successfully recovered after treatment, indicating effective clinical practices. However, continuous monitoring of treatment procedures is essential to further improve recovery rates and minimize mortality.&#10;&#10;• Departments generating higher revenue should be prioritized for infrastructure development and technological upgrades to maintain operational efficiency and improve patient satisfaction.&#10;&#10;• Uneven patient distribution across departments may lead to staff workload imbalance. Proper workforce planning and shift management can improve productivity and reduce employee burnout.&#10;&#10;• The implementation of healthcare analytics dashboards supports data-driven decision-making by providing real-time insights into hospital operations, resource utilization, and patient outcomes.' captured-sheet='Healthcare Analytics' id='11' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{C4DFBB4C-4B90-41FF-BC20-0B6423903310}' />
    </dashboard>
